-- Indian shares end at record closing high
-- By Indulal PM
-- Mon Jun 09, 2014 06:12AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 9 (Reuters) - Indian shares surged to record highs on Monday as blue chips such as Coal India <COAL.NS> and Larsen & Toubro <LART.NS> continued to rally on hopes of wide-ranging reforms by the new Narendra Modi government.

NSE index gained as much as 1.2 percent to hit an all-time high of 7,673.70, breaking the highest level touched on Friday. The index provisionally closed 0.82 percent higher at 7,645.80.